<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870707-0047 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:CMS Energy Corp.</HL><DD> 07/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CMSNUCLEAR POWER, FUEL (NUK)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><TEXT>   CMS ENERGY CORP., Jackson, Miss., said a unit of Brown Boveri andamp; Co. of Switzerland is investing $50 million to help CMS convert part of its mothballed Midland, Mich., nuclear power plant to a gas-fired facility. CMS, formerly called Consumers Power Co., said Brown Boveri will receive a 6% stake in the project. CMS Energy, whose main subsidiary is a gas and electric utility, said it plans to buy 12 gas turbines for about $150 million from Brown Boveri for the project. </TEXT></DOC>